The paper deals with communication complexity, which is a central topic in theoretical computer science and falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The problem of set disjointness is a classic problem in data structures (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC), and the paper discusses its applications in these areas. The paper also mentions the use of iterated logarithms, which is a common tool in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
